io.vertx.core.dns.impl.netty.decoder

Class RecordDecoderFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.vertx.core.dns.impl.netty.decoder.RecordDecoderFactory

  • public final class RecordDecoderFactory
extends Object
    Handles the decoding of resource records. Some default decoders are mapped to their resource types in the map decoders.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      RecordDecoderFactory()
      Creates a new RecordDecoderFactory only using the default decoders.
      RecordDecoderFactory(boolean useDefaultDecoders, Map<Integer,RecordDecoder<?>> customDecoders)
      Creates a RecordDecoderFactory using either custom resource record decoders, default decoders, or both.
      RecordDecoderFactory(Map<Integer,RecordDecoder<?>> customDecoders)
      Creates a new RecordDecoderFactory using the default decoders and custom decoders (custom decoders override defaults).

      • RecordDecoderFactory

        public RecordDecoderFactory()
        Creates a new RecordDecoderFactory only using the default decoders.

      • RecordDecoderFactory

        public RecordDecoderFactory(Map<Integer,RecordDecoder<?>> customDecoders)
        Creates a new RecordDecoderFactory using the default decoders and custom decoders (custom decoders override defaults).
        Parameters:
        customDecoders - user supplied resource record decoders, mapping the resource record's type to the decoder

      • RecordDecoderFactory

        public RecordDecoderFactory(boolean useDefaultDecoders,
                            Map<Integer,RecordDecoder<?>> customDecoders)
        Creates a RecordDecoderFactory using either custom resource record decoders, default decoders, or both. If a custom decoder has the same record type as a default decoder, the default decoder is overriden.
        Parameters:
        useDefaultDecoders - if true, adds default decoders
        customDecoders - if not null or empty, adds custom decoders
